So `state summary` uses a default limit of 200, which then calls `read_tail_events` with `limit=200`. Let me look at `read_tail_events` again. At line 1482-1495:

```rust
fn read_tail_events(path: &Path, limit: usize) -> Result<(Vec<Value>, String), String> {
    if limit == 0 {
        return crate::state::read_events_bounded(path, BOUNDED_FULL_SCAN_CAP);
    }
    let raw_lines = read_tail(path, limit)
        .map_err(|e| format!("error reading tail of {}: {e}", path.display()))?;
    let mut events = Vec::with_capacity(raw_lines.len());
    for line in &raw_lines {
        if let Ok(value) = serde_json::from_str::<Value>(line) {
            events.push(value);
        }
    }
    Ok((events, String::new()))
}
```

When `limit` is non-zero, it uses `read_tail` to read the last N lines, then for each line does `serde_json::from_str::<Value>(line)` - just raw JSON parsing. It does NOT call `compatibility_event_json_line` to normalize old-format events.

